comment_regular_data.body: Assigned people that contribute to clients, so we all can decide whether or not we need this. IMHO, as I made the PR (Ok, @Grayhatter did it a long time ago) i'm obviously for that getting merged.

Generally I like the idea of adding stickers to Tox.

Maybe it makes sense to add some size limits for stickers? This check can be done in toxcore for compatibility, e.g. refuse all sticker transfers that have file size bigger than some number.

What about other proposed features like animated stickers, sharing sticker packs with friends, etc.? IMO it would be better to think over and implement whole stickers feature together, instead of adding small peaces of functionality like that.
@grayhatter i see, I'll push a fix commit soon

Please enable the checkbox "Allow edits from maintainers." on the bottom right.

Also, I'd prefer to call this INLINE rather than STICKER. You could imagine short voice messages being of type INLINE as well, and showing up as playable message in the chat.
Bumped to 0.1.9 because this seems to be controversial, so will require some more discussion.
I think just an INLINE type would be enough.
Can you make a PR with an INLINE type? And also, discuss it with antox etc?
